  accentWord="Plumbing"
  subhead="A homeowner finds your site at midnight with water pouring through a kitchen ceiling from a burst supply pipe. They describe the flood and need someone urgently. Chat captures the callout overnight."
  scenario="It is midnight on a Thursday. An architect types: 'Hi — designing a basement conversion in North Oxford for a client. The architect drawings show a luxury bathroom in the basement: freestanding bath (Victoria + Albert Amiata), walk-in shower with body jets and rain head (Hansgrohe Raindance), wall-hung Geberit AquaClean shower WC, double vanity with undermount basins. The challenge is the drainage — the basement is below the sewer invert, so we need a macerator or pumped drainage solution. Hot water from a Megaflo Eco 300i in the plant room above. Approximately 4 by 3.5 metres. Can you handle below-ground plumbing with pumped drainage?' Without chat, he emails Friday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your experience with below-sewer-level drainage and asks about the macerator specification and the pump discharge route. He confirms Saniflo Sanicubic 1. Friday you review: North Oxford basement, V+A Amiata freestanding, Hansgrohe Raindance body jets, Geberit AquaClean, double vanity, pumped drainage Saniflo Sanicubic 1, Megaflo Eco 300i, 4×3.5m."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-website-chat/"
  tradePageUrl="/plumbing-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
